-- Turkish Stocks: Aksigorta, Bim Birlesik, Turk Hava Yollari Move
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-03-15T16:07:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-15/turkey-stocks-aksigorta-bim-birlesik-turk-hava-yollari-move.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  rose 0.7 percent to 61,279.31 at the close in Istanbul,
rising for a third day.  The following stocks are active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Aksigorta AS (AKGRT)  , an insurer part-owned by Ageas of
Belgium, added 5.1 percent to 1.85 liras, its biggest gain since
Dec. 7, after reporting net income last year surged to 32
million liras ($18 million) from 1.48 million liras a year
earlier, beating estimates.  Bim Birlesik Magazalar AS (BIMAS)  , Turkey’s biggest
discount grocer, fell 0.4 percent to 64 liras, after reaching an
all-time high yesterday. Deutsche Bank AG reduced the company to
hold from buy, with a 12-month price target of 67.75 per share.  Turk Hava Yollari (THYAO)  AO, Turkey’s national airline,
climbed 2.4 percent to 2.60 liras, after reporting passenger
numbers in the first two months of the year increased 19 percent
from a year earlier. The company said it may complete talks on a
possible stake purchase in Poland’s Polskie Linie Lotnicze LOT
SA within a month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
